ely where the correct change is clear, then test those builds.|] High VeryHigh Zero [horizon lojix criomos stack-a stack-b])) (88eq ([(Technology (Software (Operations ReleaseEngineering)))] Decision [|Component upgrade substrate is Nix-flake versions, universal to every component: each component's flake captures running-production (last known-working main, pinned), local in-development, and named variants (unstable, testing) as inputs; all upgrade sequences are expressed in this flake-input-as-deployed-version structure, and a release tags the whole dependency surface it uses. Tests run through Nix, so commit-first — uncommitted local state is invisible to the evaluator. The endgame is a workspace-owned content-addressed vertical stack: our own content-addressed store replaces Nix store-signing, composing Criome (auth), forge (build, replacing Nix builders), and sema-upgrade (DB migration) so every layer from build to authentication to distribution is in the persona vocabulary.|] High High Zero [nix flake criome forge sema-upgrade content-addressed-store])) (11m7 ([(Technology (Software (Operations ReleaseEngineering)))] Decision [Claude Code, Codex, and Pi must be updated together through CriomOS-home and the full CriomOS lock so active profiles and full-system deployments stay in sync after crashes or reboots.] High Minimum Zero [claude-code codex pi criomos-home criomos]))])